{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Speech-to-text output preserves speaker labels so summary attribution can map statements to specific attendees.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"A mock STT response with perfect diarization can hide real failures (missing/shifted speaker tags, diarization drift, provider config mismatch). This behavior depends on real model output quality from STT (and downstream use), which is not reliably captured by deterministic mocks.","test_description":"Run the service against a real multi-speaker meeting recording with known speaker turns using the real STT and summarization path. Assert that transcript segments include speaker labels and that summary attributions reference the correct attendees for sampled statements.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.2,"Agentic":0.65,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Structured summary includes at least one action item for every attendee who was assigned a task.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This is semantic extraction/completeness from natural language. Mocking the LLM would likely always pass and miss real omissions or misattributions. Correctness depends on real model behavior and variability.","test_description":"Use a real transcript (or real STT output) containing explicit task assignments to multiple attendees, run real LLM summarization, and assert each assigned attendee appears in action items with at least one associated task.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.78,"Workflow":0.07}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Key decisions in transcript appear in the summary's \"decisions\" section, not only in free-form narrative.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Section placement is an LLM structuring behavior. Deterministic mocks cannot expose real misclassification where decisions are mentioned but placed incorrectly. Real model output is required to catch this failure mode.","test_description":"Run summarization on a transcript with clearly marked decisions. Validate that those decisions are present in the dedicated `decisions` field/section and not only in narrative text.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.11,"Agentic":0.76,"Workflow":0.07}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"For audio longer than 60 minutes, service splits into segments, processes sequentially, and merges into one coherent summary.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Failure boundary spans orchestration across multiple sequential processing steps plus merge quality. Mocks can miss boundary errors (segment ordering, dropped context, merge regressions) and hide cumulative model effects across segments.","test_description":"Use a real >60-minute recording. Execute the production split->transcribe->summarize-per-segment->merge pipeline. Assert segment count/order, complete coverage (no missing time ranges), and final unified structured summary with cross-segment consistency checks.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.17,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.6}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"End-to-end pipeline (upload, transcribe, summarize, deliver structured output) runs for a real meeting recording without manual intervention.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is a full multi-stage pipeline with external APIs and multiple AI steps. Real failures often occur only in combined execution (timeouts, retries, handoff schema mismatches, partial outputs). Lower-level tests can miss these interactions.","test_description":"Run an end-to-end job in a production-like environment using a real meeting file and real dependencies. Assert successful completion state, no human retry/patch steps, and valid final structured payload containing action items, decisions, and attendee attributions.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.1,"Workflow":0.75}}]}
